news.title: Won't operate until reduction in GST, coal rates: Brick kiln owners in Ludhiana
news.para: ​The brick kiln owners are also demanding controlling of the rates of coal, which has skyrocketed recently, thereby leading to further increase in their production costs.

news.title: Kolkata civic body intensifies drive to demolish unsafe buildings
news.para: The civic body has been vacating some of the insecure buildings - parts of which have become irreparable - to prevent the loss of lives during monsoon.

news.title: Kochi: Residents looking to rise above flood risk by lifting their houses
news.para: House-lifting firms have been receiving enquiries from residents in Kadavanthra, Kaloor, Pachalam, Elamakkara and other areas in the city.

news.title: On Day 1 of its survey, Chandigarh housing board checks 576 Ram Darbar flats
news.para: The teams were carrying legal documents of flats, owners’ details, days of allotment and pictures of original allottees with them, tallying it with information given by the allottees.

news.title: As SC order draws the line, all eyes now on forest conservation act changes
news.para: The FC Amendment Bill has already been listed for introduction in the current session of Parliament, which aims to clarify the applicability of the Act in various types of land and to streamline the process of approvals under the Act.

news.title: Leasing of flexible workspace by corporate up 59% in Apr-Jun: Report
news.para: ​Enterprises had leased 17,691 seats in coworking centres in the April-June quarter of last year across eight major cities -- Delhi-NCR, Mumbai, Pune, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Chennai, Kolkata and Ahmedabad.

news.title: Max Ventures emerges top bidder for Axis Bank's land in Noida
news.para: he current land parcel is for commercial use and is next to the 7,00,000 square feet under-construction office and retail spaces of the company with New York Life Insurance Company as a financial partner.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP bans sale & purchase of properties in Sushant Lok-2
news.para: Residents of the licensed colony, however, have opposed the action, saying the town planner should impose restrictions on the developer’s properties and not theirs.

news.title: I-T dept raids Hotel Royal Plaza's chairman for stashing Rs 40 crore abroad
news.para: "Foreign Asset Investigation Units (FAIUs) of Income Tax department has conducted this search for undisclosed assets held by Mittal abroad and possessing black money in foreign shores," the I-T officials told adding that "in this regard 18 premises across Delhi, Mumbai and Daman were covered during the search operation."

news.title: Chandigarh: Special committee recommended for need-based changes in properties
news.para: On the pattern of Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB), MP Kirron Kher-led committee has recommended a special committee for need-based changes in properties under the estate office.The 11-member committee, headed by Kher, was formed on the directions of Supreme Court.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board demolishes illegal constructions in Sector 56
news.para: The board is computing the cost of demolitions which will be recovered from the allottees. In case of non-payment, their allotments could be cancelled.

news.title: Chennai Metro to lease out 2.11 lakh sq ft space at Shenoy Nagar
news.para: Officials said the underground complex built over a 4.3lakh sqft area will have a 2.1lakh sqft shopping space and 1.7lakh sqft parking area for 404 cars and 893 bikes.

news.title: Indore administration expects to earn Rs 350 crore from selling three government assets
news.para: According to senior administrative officials, as many as three properties owned by different departments of the MP Government, have been listed on MP Public Assets Management Department’s portal for auction.

news.title: Manesar: Raheja Navodaya RWA fined Rs 1 lakh for defunct sewage treatment plant
news.para: In February this year, MCM imposed a penalty of Rs 1 lakh, however at that time the STP was being operated by the builder. In April, the RWA took over the operations and maintenance of the STP but has failed to ensure environmental norms are followed.

news.title: Haryana: New policy on handover of upkeep, RWAs not enthused
news.para: The draft policy addresses the formation of the AOA, its functioning, and upkeep of common areas, and elaborates on the role of promoters vis-à-vis individual allottees and RWAs.
